{
  "texts": [
    "This gap is particularly evident in real-world applications, such as food product development or health diagnostics, where sensory responses are influenced by contextual and physiological factors.",
    "The variability in how individuals perceive taste and smell, shaped by genetics, age, and environmental exposure, creates domain shifts that traditional models are not equipped to handle.",
    "Moreover, the lack of standardized testing protocols across datasets exacerbates this issue, making it difficult to compare or replicate findings across studies.",
    "Another barrier lies in the integration of multimodal sensory data.",
    "Human perception of flavor is inherently multisensory, involving the combination of olfactory, gustatory, visual, auditory, and even somatosensory inputs."
  ]
}